          <h2>Background</h2>
          <p>
            Imagine sinking into naturally heated pools cascading down a travertine terrace, with misty forest views and the roar of the North Umpqua River below. Umpqua Hot Springs in Oregon's Umpqua National Forest delivers this magical escape, drawing adventurers for its tiered geothermal pools that range from 100 to 115 degrees Fahrenheit. As one of the state's most iconic soaking spots, it blends rugged beauty with ultimate relaxation.
          </p>

          <h2>Our Experience</h2>
          <p>
            Tucked deep in the forest near Toketee Falls, reaching Umpqua requires a short but steep 0.4 mile hike from the trailhead, complete with handrails and river views along the way. The U.S. Forest Service site details how visitors cross a colorful footbridge before climbing to the pools, which are day use only from sunrise to sunset with a $5 vehicle fee payable via Recreation.gov app or pass. Expect clothing optional vibes and high popularity, so early weekdays beat peak crowds.
          </p>
          <p>
            Guides from Soak Oregon and Lorjor Explore emphasize preparation for the rough Forest Road 3401 access, recommending high clearance vehicles and sturdy boots for the slippery trail. Multiple pools offer variety, from the hottest upper tub under a wooden shelter to cooler lower ones overlooking dancing river waters, all nestled in lush evergreens. Pack out all trash to preserve this pristine site, as amenities are basic with just vault toilets nearby.
          </p>
          <p>
            AllTrails users rave about the trail's quick reward after the ascent, noting stunning overlooks and the need to watch for mud or winter snow adding extra miles if the road gates close. Nearby Toketee Lake Campground provides convenient overnight stays. Umpqua Hot Springs stands out as a must visit for Oregon explorers seeking nature's perfect hot tub.
          </p>

          <aside class="callout callout--info">
            <h3 style="margin-top:0; font-family: var(--font-ui); font-weight: 600; font-size: var(--fs-lg);">Things to know</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Day use only from sunrise to sunset.</li>
              <li>$5 vehicle fee via Recreation.gov.</li>
              <li>Rough access road; high clearance vehicle recommended.</li>
              <li>Clothing optional.</li>
              <li>Pack out all trash.</li>
            </ul>
          </aside>

          <p>
            In summary, Umpqua Hot Springs offers an unforgettable blend of adventure and bliss amid Oregon's wild landscapes. Plan ahead for fees, weather, and etiquette to make your visit seamless and serene. Whether a solo soak or group getaway, these geothermal gems deliver pure Pacific Northwest magic.
          </p>

